@startuml petri_net_deadlock_resolution
title Petri Net Model: Deadlock Resolution\nBefore vs After adding GSE Permit Control Place

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

skinparam usecase {
    BackgroundColor<<place>> #FFFFFF
    BorderColor<<place>> #333333
    BackgroundColor<<resource>> #FFE4B5
    BorderColor<<resource>> #CC8800
    BackgroundColor<<token>> #90EE90
    BorderColor<<token>> #228B22
    BackgroundColor<<fix>> #B3FFB3
    BorderColor<<fix>> #006600
    BackgroundColor<<danger>> #FFB3B3
    BorderColor<<danger>> #CC0000
}

skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor<<transition>> #333333
    FontColor<<transition>> #FFFFFF
    BackgroundColor<<dead>> #CC0000
    FontColor<<dead>> #FFFFFF
}

' ============================================================
'  LEFT SIDE: BEFORE (with Deadlock)
' ============================================================

package "BEFORE: Deadlock Possible" as BEFORE #FFEEEE {

    usecase "Apron_Zone\n[2 tokens]" as B_apron <<danger>>
    usecase "Fuel_Free\n[1]" as B_fuel <<resource>>
    usecase "Cat_Free\n[1]" as B_cat <<resource>>
    usecase "Bag_Free\n[1]" as B_bag <<resource>>

    ' A1 operations
    usecase "A1_W_Ref" as B_a1wr <<place>>
    usecase "A1_W_Cat" as B_a1wc <<place>>
    usecase "A1_W_Bag" as B_a1wb <<place>>

    rectangle "t_A1_s_ref" as B_t1r <<transition>>
    rectangle "t_A1_s_cat" as B_t1c <<transition>>
    rectangle "t_A1_s_bag" as B_t1b <<transition>>

    usecase "A1_Refueling" as B_a1r <<place>>
    usecase "A1_Catering" as B_a1c <<place>>
    usecase "A1_Baggage" as B_a1bg <<place>>

    ' A2 operations
    usecase "A2_W_Ref" as B_a2wr <<place>>
    usecase "A2_W_Cat" as B_a2wc <<place>>
    usecase "A2_W_Bag" as B_a2wb <<place>>

    rectangle "t_A2_s_ref" as B_t2r <<transition>>
    rectangle "t_A2_s_cat" as B_t2c <<transition>>
    rectangle "t_A2_s_bag" as B_t2b <<transition>>

    usecase "A2_Refueling" as B_a2r <<place>>
    usecase "A2_Catering" as B_a2c <<place>>
    usecase "A2_Baggage" as B_a2bg <<place>>

    ' Arcs A1
    B_a1wr --> B_t1r
    B_fuel --> B_t1r
    B_apron --> B_t1r
    B_t1r --> B_a1r

    B_a1wc --> B_t1c
    B_cat --> B_t1c
    B_apron --> B_t1c
    B_t1c --> B_a1c

    B_a1wb --> B_t1b
    B_bag --> B_t1b
    B_apron --> B_t1b
    B_t1b --> B_a1bg

    ' Arcs A2
    B_a2wr --> B_t2r
    B_fuel --> B_t2r
    B_apron --> B_t2r
    B_t2r --> B_a2r

    B_a2wc --> B_t2c
    B_cat --> B_t2c
    B_apron --> B_t2c
    B_t2c --> B_a2c

    B_a2wb --> B_t2b
    B_bag --> B_t2b
    B_apron --> B_t2b
    B_t2b --> B_a2bg
}

note bottom of BEFORE
  **Deadlock Trace:**
  1. t_A1_s_ref fires -> acquires Fuel + Apron(1)
  2. t_A2_s_cat fires -> acquires Cat + Apron(2)
  3. Apron = 0 tokens left!
  4. t_A1_s_cat BLOCKED (no Apron)
  5. t_A1_s_bag BLOCKED (no Apron)
  6. t_A2_s_ref BLOCKED (no Fuel, no Apron)
  7. t_A2_s_bag BLOCKED (no Apron)
  8. A1 waits for Apron, A2 waits for Apron
  9. Nobody can release Apron -> **DEADLOCK!**
end note

' ============================================================
'  RIGHT SIDE: AFTER (Deadlock Fixed)
' ============================================================

package "AFTER: Deadlock-Free (with GSE Permit)" as AFTER #EEFFEE {

    usecase "Apron_Zone\n[2 tokens]" as A_apron <<resource>>
    usecase "Fuel_Free\n[1]" as A_fuel <<resource>>
    usecase "Cat_Free\n[1]" as A_cat <<resource>>
    usecase "Bag_Free\n[1]" as A_bag <<resource>>

    usecase "**GSE_Permit**\n**[2 tokens]**\n(Control Place)" as A_permit <<fix>>

    ' A1 operations
    usecase "A1_W_Ref" as A_a1wr <<place>>
    usecase "A1_W_Cat" as A_a1wc <<place>>
    usecase "A1_W_Bag" as A_a1wb <<place>>

    rectangle "t_A1_s_ref" as A_t1r <<transition>>
    rectangle "t_A1_s_cat" as A_t1c <<transition>>
    rectangle "t_A1_s_bag" as A_t1b <<transition>>

    usecase "A1_Refueling" as A_a1r <<place>>
    usecase "A1_Catering" as A_a1c <<place>>
    usecase "A1_Baggage" as A_a1bg <<place>>

    rectangle "t_A1_e_ref" as A_t1re <<transition>>
    rectangle "t_A1_e_cat" as A_t1ce <<transition>>
    rectangle "t_A1_e_bag" as A_t1be <<transition>>

    usecase "A1_Ref_Done" as A_a1rd <<place>>
    usecase "A1_Cat_Done" as A_a1cd <<place>>
    usecase "A1_Bag_Done" as A_a1bd <<place>>

    ' Arcs A1 with permit
    A_a1wr --> A_t1r
    A_fuel --> A_t1r
    A_apron --> A_t1r
    A_permit --> A_t1r : **acquire**
    A_t1r --> A_a1r

    A_a1wc --> A_t1c
    A_cat --> A_t1c
    A_apron --> A_t1c
    A_permit --> A_t1c : **acquire**
    A_t1c --> A_a1c

    A_a1wb --> A_t1b
    A_bag --> A_t1b
    A_apron --> A_t1b
    A_permit --> A_t1b : **acquire**
    A_t1b --> A_a1bg

    ' Release arcs
    A_a1r --> A_t1re
    A_t1re --> A_a1rd
    A_t1re --> A_fuel : release
    A_t1re --> A_apron : release
    A_t1re --> A_permit : **release**

    A_a1c --> A_t1ce
    A_t1ce --> A_a1cd
    A_t1ce --> A_cat : release
    A_t1ce --> A_apron : release
    A_t1ce --> A_permit : **release**

    A_a1bg --> A_t1be
    A_t1be --> A_a1bd
    A_t1be --> A_bag : release
    A_t1be --> A_apron : release
    A_t1be --> A_permit : **release**
}

note bottom of AFTER
  **Why it works:**
  GSE_Permit has 2 tokens = max 2 concurrent GSE ops
  (matches Apron_Zone capacity of 2)

  1. t_A1_s_ref fires -> Permit=1, Apron=1
  2. t_A1_s_cat fires -> Permit=0, Apron=0
  3. t_A2_s_* ALL BLOCKED (no Permit)
  4. A1 finishes refuel -> Permit=1, Apron=1
  5. Now A1 can do baggage OR A2 can start
  6. **No circular wait possible!**

  This is the **Ordered Resource Acquisition**
  strategy - classic deadlock prevention.
end note

@enduml
